casebody.data:
ROBERT W. THOMPSON, PLAINTIFF, v. HANS A. HESSE, DEFENDANT. Decided August 10, 1926.

Before Gummere, Chiee Justice, and Justices Kalis oh and Campbell.

Eor the rule, David M. Sterner. Contra, Carl S. Kuébler. Per Curiam.

Our examination and consideration of the proofs in this matter brings us to the conclusion that the verdict is not against the weight of the evidence, and the rule to show cause will, therefore, be discharged.
